\series default

\begin_inset Formula $(\implies)$
\end_inset

 Assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $f:A\to B$
\end_inset

 is 1-to-1.
 Suppose for contradiction that there exists 
\begin_inset Formula $y\in B$
\end_inset

 so that 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{-1}(\{y\})$
\end_inset

