 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{1},a_{2}\in f^{-1}(\{y\})$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{1}\neq a_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 By definition of 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{-1}(\{y\})$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $f(a_{1})=y=f(a_{2})$
\end_inset

, though 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{1}\neq a_{2}$
\end_inset

.
